While the COVID-19 pandemic has changed the district‚Äôs short-term operations, our long-term facility needs remain. Fox C-6‚Äôs no tax increase bond issue (Prop P) on the rescheduled June 2 ballot includes the following projects for Meramec Heights Elementary.

1. Partial rebuild of the building, including new classrooms
2. Making Meramec Heights Elementary ADA compliant
3. Reconstruct main entrance for security
4. Expand security camera system
5. Exterior door key card access system

For a complete list of projects for the district, visit www.foxc6propp.org.

Remember to vote on June 2, 2020.

Each year, the Fox C-6 School District recognizes members of our community (staff, students, parents, or community members) who contribute to Fox C-6 PROMISE that all students will leave Fox schools with a PURPOSE. The award is a small way to show our appreciation to those who have excelled in their pursuit of making Fox C-6 Schools the best it can be.

Over 200 Fox C-6 community members including teachers, support staff members, parents, students, and volunteers were nominated for a Masterpiece Award this year. Follow along as Fox C-6 Superintendent Dr. Nisha Patel surprises the 10 Masterpiece Award winners.

Fox C-6 Superintendent Dr. Nisha Patel selects one Fox community member each year to honor with the Superintendent's Choice Masterpiece Award. This year, she selected the Fox C-6 Director of Information/Technology, Luke Heitert.

Luke Heitert, YOU are a Masterpiece Award winner! Congratulations!

Luke Heitert, YOU are a Masterpiece Award winner! Congratulations!

Listen to this episode at bit.ly/37f8x8P.

Subscribe wherever you listen to podcasts or visit http://fox.k12.mo.us/podcast for more!
